Jack O'Brien (wrestler) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jack_O%27Brien_(wrestler) 0 Marcelo Andreani (February 18, 1910 – September 24, 1982) was an Italian-born Mexican professional wrestler best known under the ring name "Roughouse" Jack O'Brien and worked mainly in Mexico for Empresa Mexicana de Lucha Libre (EMLL) where he held the Mexican National Lightweight Championship, Mexican National Welterweight Championship and NWA World Welterweight Championship twice during his career that spanned from 1934 until 1956. O'Brien is credited with inventing the Abdominal Stretch, or Tirabuzón (Spanish for "Corkscrew").
